nt-size:13px;line-height:1.7;margin-top:10px;'>A snapshot forward P/E tells you the price but not the direction. The direction of analyst estimate revisions is what actually predicts whether that multiple expands or compresses. When analysts raise estimates month after month — that's capitulation: they were wrong, they're admitting it, and the market prices in the move before the estimate update catches up. That's how VERA trades at a premium even before approval: the buyside has been building since ORIGIN data, not waiting for consensus. Contrast with VRDN: estimates were cut 17–20% after REVEAL-1 disappointment, and the stock tracked those cuts from $24 down to $16. Same sector, same PDUFA week, but the revision momentum told the whole story. If veligrotug gets approved June 30, VRDN's estimates reverse instantly — revision momentum flips from headwind to tailwind in a single session, and that re-rating is violent.</div><div style='background:#0f172a;border-radius:4px;padding:10px;margin-top:12px;'><div style='color:#94a3b8;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;'>Also today:</div><div style='color:#cbd5e1;font-size:12px;margin-top:4px;'><strong style='color:#f1f5f9;'>Beat-and-raise</strong> — when a company beats earnings AND raises forward guidance simultaneously. The strongest signal in equities. The biotech equivalent: Phase 3 hits primary endpoint AND the company announces accelerated commercial launch timeline. VERA pulled this double with atacicept: positive ORIGIN data + FDA priority review + BTD + director open-market buys. That stacked signal is why 13 analysts are Strong Buy with zero sells.</div></div></td></tr><!-- FOOTER --><tr><td style='background:#0f172a;padding:14px 28px;border-radius:0 0 10px 10px;'><div style='color:#475569;font-size:10px;line-height:1.7;'><strong style='color:#64748b;'>Prices as of:</strong> NYSE close June 25, 2026 (June 26 final prices not yet indexed at run time)<br><strong style='color:#